{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"alias":"unchildish-thievish-nautilus","description":"## Context\nEnvironment signing keys rotate using era-scoped validity (valid-at-log-position, not wall-clock) so past certificates keep verifying and rotated-out keys cannot sign new ones.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Env-key rotation uses era-scoped validity; a cert from a key valid at its era verifies while one past its rotation does not (test).\n- [ ] Rotation is documented; no trusted-clock dependency.","id":"5893-f6d4-f2f3-4542","parent_id":"6d0d-7580-e18f-48c3","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"task","title":"op-cert: environment-key era-scoped rotation"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783735899714437001,"uuid":"861e8ee8-c414-4fbd-b685-57dfc7ab988a"}